This paper deals with covert transmission, energy harvesting, and relay communication, which are all topics that fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the performance limits and associated costs of achieving covert transmission, which can be considered as a system-level problem and falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the detection error probability, which is a security-related metric and falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the energy conversion efficiency, which is a metric related to hardware and falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
